ygData.messageBody:
Hello Tszaaz,

"Actually I would like to request folks offer little
detail besides the zone (unless something is a
deathtrap for a level 17, THAT would be appreciated)
as exploring is 90 percent of the fun."

Have you taken dive into Lake Rathe? There are some
interesting things there. There are some dangers but
most if not all can avoided or dealt with if you keep
an eye on where you are. There are also rumors of a
sea monster, but I have heard some say it was just in
beta. Don't know for sure. But I do know I have been
swimming there a long time and have never seen
anything like that. Its an interesting zone if you
have never been. If you go you might see tons of
people of there. But don't let that fool you. 99% of
the people will be sitting on top of each other at the
gnoll camp :) Leaving you, for the most part, with the
run of the zone.

Safe travels,
Kobias
Lvl 9 Bard
Innoruuk
